disclaimer.title = You must read the following before making a claim
disclaimer.heading = You must read the following before making a claim
disclaimer.heading.after = Claiming tax relief on or after 6 April 2022
disclaimer.notification.title = Guidance has changed from 6 April 2022
disclaimer.notification.text = The guidance for claiming tax relief for working from home has changed for expenses on or after 6 April 2022.
disclaimer.info.text.1 = You can claim if your employer has not already paid your expenses and you have additional household costs as a result of working from home.
disclaimer.info.text.2 = To claim tax relief, you cannot have just chosen to work from home.
disclaimer.bullet.heading = One of the following rules must also apply:
disclaimer.bullet.text.1 = there are no appropriate facilities available for you to perform your job on your employer’s premises
disclaimer.bullet.text.2 = the nature of the job requires you to live so far from the employer’s premises that it is unreasonable for you to travel to those premises on a daily basis
disclaimer.bullet.text.3 = you are required, under government restrictions, to work from home
disclaimer.heading.before = Claiming tax relief on or before 5 April 2022
disclaimer.bullet.heading.1 = You can claim if all the following rules apply:
disclaimer.bullet.text.4 = your employer has not already paid your expenses
disclaimer.bullet.text.5 = government guidelines or your employer have required you to work from home or self-isolate
disclaimer.bullet.text.6 = you have additional household costs as a result of working from home
disclaimer.warning.text.1 = Guidance has changed from 6 April 2022.
disclaimer.warning.text.2 = You must ensure you meet the rules for claiming, as you may be prosecuted if you deliberately give incorrect or misleading information.
disclaimer.accept.text.1 = By clicking accept and continue, you are accepting that you meet the rules for the years you are claiming for.
